<TD CLASS="log">

 <table width="100%"><tr><td class="menuhead">&nbsp;The data-zoid.com guide to using footpaths/sidewalks.</td></tr></table><BR>
<span class="reg">I've just spent a week in Sydney. If I've noticed nothing else about the people of this fine city, it's the overall lack of footpath ettiquette. Read, learn, pass on the knowledge. You'll feel better.<br />
<br />
<b>1. If you're on the footpath, FUCKING WALK.</b><br />
<br />
Footpaths are for people in motion. Do not stop on a footpath, chat on a footpath, sit on a footpath, lie on a footpath, defecate on a footpath or otherwise obstruct a footpath. This goes tenfold when it's actually a busy footpath, particularly of the type found in railway stations, or the type facilitated by the narrow hallways in say - the Queen Victoria Building. <br />
<br />
Simple principle of physics, matter cannot pass through matter. If you're standing in someone's way, they CANNOT WALK THROUGH YOU, dumbarse.<br />
<br />
<b>2. If you're walking on the footpath, actually walk somewhere.</b><br />
<br />
Plan ahead before traipsing. Consider deciding upon a destination. Human beings are not equipped with indicator lights, so the pedestrians behind you cannot actually tell where you're turning. Yes, you could shout "I'M TURNING LEFT AT THE NEWSAGENT ENTRANCE", but you'll wind up looking like a tit. This will be covered at a later time, in "The data-zoid.com guide to avoiding looking like a tit in public". <br />
<br />
<b>3. If you're walking, walk in the same direction until you reach your destination.</b><br />
<br />
If you decide to change destination, or discover you've walked the wrong way/too far/whatever, pull over to the "shoulder" of the footpath, or anywhere where you're not obstructing people before you turn around and attempt to swathe through the traffic in the opposite direction. The people behind you do not really wish to slam face-first into your shoulder blades the split second you realise "The Body Shop" was two doors back.<br />
<br />
<b>4. For the love of Jesus Christ sat naked on a q-tip, KEEP TO THE LEFT*.</b><br />
<br />
Anywhere where the pedestrian traffic is heavy enough to warrant following a fat person because they act as a shield against oncoming speedy (and/or blind) powerwalkers is a place where lanes should be enforced. KEEP TO THE LEFT if you're going forward. Otherwise, walk backwards.<br />
<br />
* Right in the U.S and other backwards nations.<br />
<br />
<b>5. Obey the unwritten rules of pedestrianising.</b><br />
<br />
Simple, little rules. Maybe you should write them down. On post-its. And pin them to your feet, so you can read them while you shuffle through the peak-hour pedlock of Town Hall station at 1630 hours.<br />
<br />
- <b>Dont break up couples.</b><br />
Romantic notion, no? "Couples" consitute any pair of people obviously connected in some way. Two people with the same uniform. Two people talking to each other. Two people throwing fisticuffs at each other. Two people holding hands (if nothing else, personal injury could result from the latter). Parents and their children. DO NOT WALK BETWEEN THEM. Be polite, for fuck's sake.<br />
<br />
- <b>Don't spit on people.</b><br />
Seriously. I don't know why I even have to add this, but hey - keep your expectoration to yourself. Someone else's phlegm is not conducive to a pleasant day.<br />
<br />
- <b>Don't drop things.</b><br />
Avoid dropping things. Unlike the movies, real life doesn't have a clause that reads 'every pretty girl who drops paperwork in pedestrian traffic will meet her handsome prince'. In fact, it's written in bold that 'every pretty girl who drops anything that isn't her trousers in pedestrian traffic will likely become part of the pavement'. Sorry, ladies.<br />
<br />
<b>6. Be. Fucking. Polite. Just for once.</b><br />
<br />
Smile, or something. Stop walking around aimlessly like a horse just shat in your handbag. The world's depressing enough without your dour facade adding to it.<br />
<br />
Walk in peace. <IMG SRC="yahoo_happy.gif" ALIGN="middle"></span><BR><BR>
